originalText.text: I was extremely disappointed with the service at Concerto garage. I was at John jay for a soccer tournament today and I was told across the street they only charge 12$ for those who are at John jay for the day. Therefore, I decided to park right across the street. When I went to pick up my car, first, the valet was flying with car up the ramp and then I noticed a mark on my car door. The mark looked like dirt then I came home cleaned it off and there’s now paint missing from my door. I would’ve been better off parking on the street or just taking the subway. Never again. They bring you in with the price just don’t fall for the bait.

originalText.text:
Don't park here. I left my car for three hours tonight  to return to it not being able to start. I first attempted to jump the battery since they wouldn't. Then I realized the key, which needs to be inside the car for it to start, wasn't inside the car. I asked the attendant to give me the key, and he insisted it was inside the vehicle but would not help me locate it.  They apparently leave all the keys in the cars without tags or a board. I asked for management phone number and they said there was none.

Finally I left to get a second key (a $65 cab ride way way uptown). When I returned it was running... they told me they jumped it, and it cost $50. (We  had asked them to jump it in the first 10 minutes of it not starting so why would they do it now when I'm not here?) When I blew my top, he said $20. It definitely felt like extortion or some scam going on.

All of the warning lights in the car were on but I took a chance because I needed to get the hell outta there. The warning lights turned off by the time I got home but I still have yet to find the key.

Do yourself a favor and pay more $$ for another lot in the area. It's not worth the headache.

originalText.text: I use this parking lot 1-2 times a month. I usually do not have a problem.  The last time I used this parking lot I was charged $19.00 for an hour and a half.  The attendant told me that the prices went up.  Even though the rates are displayed on the wall, which indicate $10.67 for an hour, $ 14.95 for up to two hours, and $19.08 for up to 10 hours.  I have used all of these rates and was charged correctly in the past.  Be careful, if you use this garage, ask the price before hand, take a picture of your ticket for proof of time and date, and ask for a receipt.  I am filing a complaint with the city. Some of their employees are very nice and others can not be trusted!!

originalText.text: Asked if they had an available charger for my EV and they said “you don’t need a charge.” That was a surprise to me because my battery was low. Not sure how you can tell just by looking at a car that it doesn’t need a charge. I promptly left and parked at the next garage.
